.TH "insert" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
insert \- Insert record or records into the current collection.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]db.collectionspace.collection.insert(<doc|docs>,[flag])\f[]
.PP
\f[B]db.collectionspace.collection.insert(<doc|docs>,[options])\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Collection
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Insert record or records into the current collection.
If the current collection does not exist, please create it first.
.SH PARAMETERS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]doc/docs\f[] ( \f[I]Object/Array of Object\f[]， \f[I]Required\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
Record or records to be inserted.
Can not be null.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]flag\f[] ( \f[I]Int32\f[]， \f[I]Optional\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
Insert flag, use to control the behavior and result of inserting.
Can be the follow value:
.IP \[bu] 2
0, default value.
.IP \[bu] 2
SDB_INSERT_RETURN_ID, means return the value of "_id" field of the record.
.IP \[bu] 2
SDB_INSERT_CONTONDUP, means continue inserting (no errors were reported) when
hitting index key duplicate error.
.IP \[bu] 2
SDB_INSERT_REPLACEONDUP, means replace the exist value to the inserting value
when hitting index key duplicate error, and continue the left records (no errors
were reported).
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]options\f[] ( \f[I]Object\f[]， \f[I]Optional\f[] )
.RS 2
Insert options, use to control the behavior and result of inserting.
So far, its role is consistent with the argument \f[C]flag\f[], and it can be
the follow value:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]ReturnOID\f[] ( \f[I]Bool\f[], \f[I]Optional\f[] ): the same with
"SDB_INSERT_RETURN_ID" in argument \f[C]flag\f[].
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]ContOnDup\f[] ( \f[I]Bool\f[], \f[I]Optional\f[] ): the same with
"SDB_INSERT_CONTONDUP" in argument \f[C]flag\f[].
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]ReplaceOnDup\f[] ( \f[I]Bool\f[], \f[I]Optional\f[] ): the same with
"SDB_INSERT_REPLACEONDUP" in argument \f[C]flag\f[].
.RE
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.IP \[bu] 2
When the provided record does not have an "_id" field, the database will add one
for it.
.IP \[bu] 2
When inserting a single record, the available flag
is：SDB_INSERT_RETURN_ID、SDB_INSERT_REPLACEONDUP; When inserting multiple
records, the available flag contains all flags.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, the follow result will be returned:
.IP \[bu] 2
When using "SDB_INSERT_RETURN_ID" in flag or "ReturnOID" in options to control
the insert behavior and result, a Json object will be returned.
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
for single inserting: return the value of field "_id".
.IP \[bu] 2
for bulk inseting: return the value of field "_id" by array.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Void for the other situations.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
the exceptions of \f[C]insert()\f[] are as below:
